body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue
In the file my_pkg.sv I have the following

package my_pkg;
       parameter KL=64;
endpackage

in the file top.sv I have the following
import my_pkg::*;
module top(
        input logic i_clk,
        output logic o_done
);
endmodule


## Expected behavior
The tool should accept the top level file since it is a valid syntax. This is a common way to import all the content of a package inside a module and hence avoid having to prefix the package name every time a package parameter is used inside the module. This works in Modelsim, VCS as well as in DC. Is there a way to accomplish this in Yosys?
## Actual behavior

top.sv:1: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected TOK_ID
